  The zero-inflated Poisson distribution is given by

  <\equation>
    <tabular|<tformat|<table|<row|<cell|P<around*|(|Z<rsub|t>=i|)>=>|<cell|<choice|<tformat|<table|<row|<cell|<around*|(|1-p|)>+p
    e<rsup|-\<lambda\>>>|<cell|i=0>>|<row|<cell|p<frac|e<rsup|-\<lambda\>>\<lambda\><rsup|i>|i!>>|<cell|i\<geqslant\>1>>>>>>>>>>
  </equation>

  with a marginal mean\ 

  <\equation>
    \<mu\><rsub|Z>=p \<lambda\>
  </equation>

  and variance

  <\equation*>
    <tabular|<tformat|<table|<row|<cell|\<sigma\><rsub|Z><rsup|2>>|<cell|=\<mu\><rsub|Z>+p<around*|(|1-p|)>\<lambda\><rsup|2>>>|<row|<cell|>|<cell|=p
    \<lambda\>+p<around*|(|1-p|)>\<lambda\><rsup|2>>>>>>
  </equation*>

